history.content:
I was just wondering which of these two schedules will be more doable.

INDENG185 is described this way: 

In this highly experiential course, students work in simulated start-up teams to create products or start-up ideas to address a broadly-defined need of an industry partner or social challenge.

If I take CS61c and CS188 this fall, I'll end up taking CS160 and CS170 in the spring. 

If I take CS61c and CS160 this fall, I'll end up taking CS188 and CS170 in the spring.

I'm trying to plan my classes for this fall with Spring 2019 in mind.
history.subject: CS61c + CS188 + INDENG185 VERSUS CS61c + CS160 + INDENG185
